# UI Components and Styling

## Component Library
- Use components from [components/ui/](mdc:components/ui/) directory
- Built with Radix UI primitives and Tailwind CSS
- Consistent design system with orange accent color

## Styling Conventions
- Use Tailwind CSS classes for styling
- Follow the existing color scheme (orange primary, gray neutrals)
- Use consistent spacing and typography scales
- Implement responsive design with mobile-first approach

## Component Patterns
```typescript
// Button component usage
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';

<Button variant="default" size="lg" className="custom-class">
  Button Text
</Button>
```

## Form Components
- Use `Input` and `Label` components for form fields
- Implement proper form validation with error states
- Use consistent form styling and spacing

## Loading States
- Use `Suspense` boundaries for loading states
- Implement skeleton loaders for better UX
- Show loading spinners for async operations

## Error States
- Display user-friendly error messages
- Use consistent error styling (red text, error icons)
- Provide actionable error recovery options

## Accessibility
- Use proper ARIA labels and roles
- Ensure keyboard navigation works
- Maintain good color contrast ratios
- Use semantic HTML elements

## Icons
- Use Lucide React icons consistently
- Import specific icons: `import { Upload, FolderOpen } from 'lucide-react'`
- Use appropriate icon sizes and colors